The paper discusses the application of deep learning techniques, specifically memory-augmented neural networks, for solving various process analytics related problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with data security and privacy concerns related to process analytics, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of real-world datasets and benchmarking against state-of-the-art methods suggests that the paper could also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for the proposed approach to be used in enterprise-specific process analytics applications, which could place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
